### 🟡 7. No Global Error Handler — Potential Stack Trace Leakage (OWASP A05)

Without a catch-all error handler, Express may return a full stack trace to the client on an unhandled exception, leaking internal file paths, package versions, and logic clues.

**Fix — add a global error handler as the last middleware:**

```js
// ✅ Must be defined AFTER all routes
app.use((err, req, res, next) => {
  // Log internally with full detail
  console.error({ message: err.message, stack: err.stack, url: req.url });

  // Return a generic message to the client
  const statusCode = err.status || 500;
  res.status(statusCode).json({
    error: process.env.NODE_ENV === 'production'
      ? 'An unexpected error occurred'
      : err.message,           // only expose detail in dev/test
  });
});
```

